1
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:01,600
Despair and hunger

2
00:01:03,320 --> 00:01:05,200
can drive people to madness.

3
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:07,080
So you're saying

4
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,330
Zhang Jinxi starved you on purpose

5
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:10,520
just to watch you

6
00:01:10,520 --> 00:01:12,240
kill and hurt each other?

7
00:01:12,720 --> 00:01:14,780
Then when you and He Xiaolian got out,

8
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:17,820
you didn't do the same thing, did you?

9
00:01:23,880 --> 00:01:25,280
Hurry up.

10
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:32,000
From today on,

11
00:01:32,360 --> 00:01:34,000
you owe me your life.

12
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:47,759
Xiaolian.

13
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:49,600
Xiaolian.

14
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:57,120
Let's just say

15
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:01,160
we were a little luckier.

16
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:03,320
A new girl

17
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:05,580
caught the plague as soon as she arrived.

18
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:08,440
If he hadn't been short-handed back then,

19
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:10,240
I... I would have died long ago.

20
00:02:11,640 --> 00:02:13,900
He made us take on different identities.

21
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:17,040
To avoid drawing attention to the noodle shop,

22
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:19,400
he arranged for us to live elsewhere.

23
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:21,840
Since you got out,

24
00:02:22,079 --> 00:02:24,210
why didn't you report it to the police?

25
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,920
No one would have believed me.

26
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:30,000
The police wouldn't believe it.

27
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:31,200
Even reporters thought

28
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:33,000
it was just a made-up story.

29
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:36,600
Because none of us

30
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:39,280
knew where that cell was.

31
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:45,200
Except for picking up goods at the noodle shop,

32
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:47,600
we were forbidden from meeting privately.

33
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:49,560
At first,

34
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:52,400
he had people watching us.

35
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:55,440
It wasn't until He Xiaolian and I

36
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:57,300
had completed over a hundred jobs

37
00:02:58,120 --> 00:03:00,250
that he slowly stopped suspecting us.

38
00:03:02,160 --> 00:03:02,800
Cuckoo.

39
00:03:03,160 --> 00:03:03,800
Cuckoo.

40
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:09,520
Are they all asleep?

41
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:11,120
Yes, they are.

42
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:13,280
I left the dictionary and books

43
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:15,280
at the noodle shop entrance.

44
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:16,880
Remember to pick them up.

45
00:03:18,480 --> 00:03:19,440
Don't slack off.

46
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:21,720
You've been memorizing place names for two months,

47
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:23,440
and still haven't remembered them.

48
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:25,480
I'll come back to quiz you next time.

49
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:26,800
Shanghai is too big.

50
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:28,320
I can never remember.

51
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,520
Xiaolian made this spider for you.

52
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:41,480
She told me

53
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:44,280
it's a spider that will never die.

54
00:03:45,079 --> 00:03:46,840
She's so childish.

55
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:49,100
It looks exactly like Xiaowu.

56
00:03:53,079 --> 00:03:54,280
Sis, I have to go back.

57
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:54,960
Okay.

58
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,260
According to Haitang,

59
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:16,959
this cell is damp all year round

60
00:04:16,959 --> 00:04:18,360
and never sees sunlight.

61
00:04:19,440 --> 00:04:20,480
So I suspect

62
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:22,610
this cell is very likely underground.

63
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:23,560
In that case,

64
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:25,220
I will send all my brothers out

65
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:27,040
to look for houses with cellars.

66
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:28,850
That search area is way too big.

67
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:34,840
Dispose far, bury near.

68
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:36,600
The reason Zhang Jinxi buried the body

69
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:37,880
in his own backyard

70
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:40,040
was because he felt closer meant safer.

71
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:40,520
That means...

72
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:41,650
the cellar is inside

73
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:42,810
the noodle shop.

74
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:44,600
Bao.

75
00:05:16,520 --> 00:05:17,680
Later, Shisan

76
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:20,640
saw Xiaolian get killed.

77
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:30,720
Zhao.

78
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:32,120
Zhao.

79
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:35,380
I'm almost done digging here.

80
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:37,260
Stop digging. Do it later.

81
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:38,970
Stretch this out for me.

82
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:50,680
This is worth

83
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:52,480
over a dozen gold bars.

84
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:08,360
Sister.

85
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:10,600
Let's just leave.

86
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:11,880
I'm afraid

87
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:14,920
you'll be the next one.

88
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:19,760
Shisan is truly scared.

89
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:23,480
He's afraid I'll be the next one lying there.

90
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:25,970
But Xiaolian can't die in vain.

91
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:28,800
That idiot Comprador Zhou, every time,

92
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:31,460
he insists on pulling out the fish guts himself.

93
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:33,360
But if you pull the guts

94
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:35,620
just a little faster, they break easily.

95
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:38,659
He did the same thing to me before.

96
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:40,880
I just remembered.

97
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:44,320
He took me to Baogong Workshop before

98
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:45,920
to see that Guan Gong Statue.

99
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:50,480
It just so happened that the next day

100
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:53,600
was the grand opening.

101
00:06:53,640 --> 00:06:55,600
We dug up the corpse

102
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:57,760
and swapped out the Guan Gong Statue.

103
00:06:57,760 --> 00:07:00,290
I couldn't even take a shower because of that.

104
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:03,600
Haitang.

105
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:06,720
I'm a bit tired today.

106
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:09,010
Why don't you go back first?

107
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:11,040
I'll pick you up in a few days.

108
00:07:11,760 --> 00:07:12,600
Alright.

109
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:14,600
I haven't seen you for a few days,

110
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:16,440
and you've grown bold, haven't you?

111
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:18,320
You're not begging me anymore.

112
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:21,520
Have you been out there

113
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:23,380
messing around with other women?

114
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:25,560
How is that possible?

115
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:27,000
I've been dying to see you.

116
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:27,440
How could I?

117
00:07:27,440 --> 00:07:28,480
Enough nonsense.

118
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:30,180
I'm going to take a shower.

119
00:07:49,400 --> 00:07:51,200
You wanted to frame Comprador Zhou.

120
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:52,530
You already succeeded.

121
00:07:52,840 --> 00:07:54,370
Why did you have to kill him?

122
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:55,920
I didn't expect

123
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:57,850
Comprador Zhou to find out so soon.

124
00:07:58,240 --> 00:07:59,400
He asked to meet me.

125
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,800
I got Thirteen before I went.

126
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:06,320
But I didn't expect that as soon as we met...

127
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:07,960
Tired of living, huh?

128
00:08:10,440 --> 00:08:11,570
You've gone too far.

129
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:16,440
I don't understand.

130
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:18,040
Why frame me?

131
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:52,560
Thirteen!

132
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:54,440
Thirteen!

133
00:08:54,680 --> 00:08:55,810
It's not your fault.

134
00:08:56,680 --> 00:08:57,840
It's all them.

135
00:08:59,520 --> 00:09:01,520
They forced us.

136
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:21,800
Thirteen.

137
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:23,640
The police might not find anything today.

138
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:24,160
Go.

139
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:26,600
Forget everything that happened today.

140
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:28,200
I'll come find you later.

141
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:29,200
Do you understand?

142
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:29,880
Go.

143
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:31,440
Inspector Lin.

144
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:34,200
Thirteen killed Comprador Zhou to save me.

145
00:09:34,520 --> 00:09:36,520
I planned everything.

146
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:38,480
If you can save him,

147
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:40,560
I will accept any punishment.

148
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:42,820
You're not the one to be punished.

149
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:45,140
It's Zhang Jinxi and Comprador Zhou.

150
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:04,680
Bao.

151
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,890
What is being offered here?

152
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:22,970
What is this?

153
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:27,280
This...

154
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:33,880
It's...

155
00:10:36,280 --> 00:10:37,140
Don't touch it.

156
00:10:37,520 --> 00:10:38,360
What's wrong?

157
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:43,660
I think Zhang Jinxi might be a eunuch.

158
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:54,640
Child.

159
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:58,560
Nothing in this world comes free.

160
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:02,000
I've let you live a good life with me.

161
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:06,120
Why are you so desperate to leave me?

162
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:08,680
So, you are

163
00:11:08,920 --> 00:11:10,850
the eunuch mentioned in the books.

164
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:13,880
Without a grandson like me,

165
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:16,690
I doubt anyone would believe you're a man.

166
00:11:18,680 --> 00:11:20,840
I am a man.

167
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:23,720
I was born a man.

168
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:27,120
Always will be.

169
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:33,290
It's a specimen.

170
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:37,130
Do you remember what Haitang just told us?

171
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:40,360
This must be what Zhang Shisan left behind.

172
00:13:02,920 --> 00:13:03,920
Here we are.

173
00:13:04,560 --> 00:13:05,840
Detectives.

174
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:07,440
How were my noodles?

175
00:13:08,920 --> 00:13:11,160
Did they suit your taste?

176
00:13:13,480 --> 00:13:14,740
Where is Zhang Shisan?

177
00:13:14,880 --> 00:13:16,160
Don't rush.

178
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:19,720
Haste makes waste.

179
00:13:20,360 --> 00:13:21,680
That kid is tough.

180
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:23,420
A little while won't hurt.

181
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:24,280
Come.

182
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:25,880
Child.

183
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:28,360
Sit here.

184
00:13:29,920 --> 00:13:30,920
Keep me company.

185
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:32,800
Let's talk.

186
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,520
Around me,

187
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:36,560
every day,

188
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:39,840
it's either mutes

189
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:42,240
or blockheads.

190
00:13:43,240 --> 00:13:45,320
I have so much to say,

191
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:47,600
but no one to listen.

192
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:48,880
Today,

193
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:51,200
I'm going to tell you everything.

194
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:52,240
Save it.

195
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:54,440
We know everything you've done.

196
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:56,440
What do you know?

197
00:13:58,080 --> 00:14:00,960
I just wanted to do honest business.

198
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:02,840
But you people

199
00:14:03,320 --> 00:14:05,600
insist on making trouble for me.

200
00:14:05,880 --> 00:14:07,010
Kidnapping, abuse,

201
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:08,560
illegal imprisonment,

202
00:14:08,560 --> 00:14:09,440
selling opium.

203
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:11,380
What kind of business is that?

204
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:12,960
What do you know?

205
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:15,480
I'm doing good deeds.

206
00:14:15,560 --> 00:14:16,640
Great deeds.

207
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:18,360
If it weren't for me,

208
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:20,640
would they be alive today?

209
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:23,840
You people

210
00:14:24,520 --> 00:14:26,450
just can't stand seeing me do well.

211
00:14:26,760 --> 00:14:29,200
I just wanted a full meal.

212
00:14:29,320 --> 00:14:30,800
Is that so hard?

213
00:14:34,280 --> 00:14:36,160
Xiaoliuzi sent stuff home again.

214
00:14:36,840 --> 00:14:38,840
Does being a eunuch pay that well?

215
00:14:40,720 --> 00:14:42,600
That red cloth is beautiful.

216
00:14:43,560 --> 00:14:44,880
What is a eunuch?

217
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:47,460
Someone who's an official in the palace.

218
00:14:47,760 --> 00:14:48,440
Look.

219
00:14:48,520 --> 00:14:49,720
They have meat to eat.

220
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:53,380
I want to go to the Forbidden City too.

221
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:05,080
Do you see these shoes?

222
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:07,280
Do they look nice?

223
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:09,240
I thought

224
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:10,880
these feet of mine

225
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:13,180
were meant to wear official shoes

226
00:15:13,680 --> 00:15:15,280
and walk on blue tiles.

227
00:15:37,320 --> 00:15:37,800
You.

228
00:15:38,400 --> 00:15:39,960
How dare you!

229
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:43,320
You dare touch what the Emperor bestowed upon me?

230
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,240
Your Majesty.

231
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:47,480
I have soiled your gift.

232
00:15:47,840 --> 00:15:48,560
I...

233
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:51,040
...deserve to die for my sins!

234
00:15:52,360 --> 00:15:53,280
It's hard.

235
00:15:54,280 --> 00:15:55,720
Living is hard.

236
00:15:56,480 --> 00:15:57,810
Not being able to die...

237
00:15:58,840 --> 00:16:00,120
...is also hard.

238
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:10,530
Fifty boxes.

239
00:16:10,920 --> 00:16:11,720
All here.

240
00:16:18,760 --> 00:16:19,690
Thank you, boss.

241
00:16:20,280 --> 00:16:22,560
Guangming Match Factory is hiring long-term workers!

242
00:16:22,560 --> 00:16:24,890
Twelve silver dollars a month per person!

243
00:16:24,920 --> 00:16:25,920
Those who want to go,

244
00:16:25,920 --> 00:16:26,720
follow me.

245
00:16:27,480 --> 00:16:27,960
Me!

246
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:29,000
I'll go!

247
00:16:29,760 --> 00:16:30,320
Okay.

248
00:16:30,720 --> 00:16:31,280
You can come too.

249
00:16:31,280 --> 00:16:32,210
I'll go! I'll go!

250
00:16:33,840 --> 00:16:34,440
Come here.

251
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:35,610
Turn around.

252
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:37,480
Turn again.

253
00:16:39,320 --> 00:16:39,760
Okay.

254
00:16:39,760 --> 00:16:40,320
Go in.

255
00:16:40,760 --> 00:16:41,440
Next.

256
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:43,130
Stand still.

257
00:16:45,320 --> 00:16:46,120
Hurry up.

258
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:47,660
Did you hear me?

259
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:48,920
Take off your pants.

260
00:16:48,920 --> 00:16:49,650
Stand still.

261
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:55,800
I won't take them off.

262
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:56,480
I quit.

263
00:16:56,720 --> 00:16:57,780
I'm not doing this.

264
00:16:58,960 --> 00:16:59,640
Come back!

265
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:02,080
Fine if you don't want the job.

266
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:03,210
Five silver dollars

267
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:04,569
to let you leave.

268
00:17:09,440 --> 00:17:10,800
Don't have it, huh?

269
00:17:15,920 --> 00:17:17,640
So you're a eunuch.

270
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:47,330
I won't do it!

271
00:17:48,320 --> 00:17:48,880
I won't!

272
00:17:49,840 --> 00:17:50,520
I won't!

273
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:51,960
I won't!

274
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:53,640
I won't!

275
00:17:54,320 --> 00:17:54,960
I won't!

276
00:18:42,960 --> 00:18:44,320
Just one puff.

277
00:18:44,320 --> 00:18:45,520
Give me a puff, quick.

278
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:49,680
Please.

279
00:18:50,040 --> 00:18:50,800
Have mercy.

280
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:52,560
Give me a puff.

281
00:18:54,120 --> 00:18:55,120
Let me have a puff.

282
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:56,620
Just a puff.

283
00:18:57,160 --> 00:18:58,000
Give me a puff.

284
00:18:58,360 --> 00:18:59,160
I'm begging you.

285
00:18:59,160 --> 00:18:59,960
Just one puff.

286
00:18:59,960 --> 00:19:00,760
Just one puff.

287
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:03,880
A bowl of rice,

288
00:19:04,840 --> 00:19:06,360
half a steamed bun,

289
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:08,400
a little bit of opium,

290
00:19:08,880 --> 00:19:10,160
can make a person

291
00:19:10,440 --> 00:19:12,880
forget about life and death.
